    <text id="A1419T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Carroll asks for clothing to be sent to him in camp and also reports on the
                    whereabouts of various individuals.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-07-30">July 30 1864</date>
                        <name type="place">
                            <orig reg="Camp Chase">camp chase</orig>
                            <orig reg="Ohio">ohio</orig>
                        </name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Mrs Virginia Miller</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>PS Send then By Express your kind letter came to hand <orig reg="today">to
                    day</orig> &amp; found me in good health hoping this may <add hand="h1"
                        place="inline">find</add> you and your family the same you stated in your
                    letter you would send me some clothing I would be <orig reg="very">verry</orig>
                    thankful to you for doing so you wanted to <orig reg="know">now</orig> what I
                    needed the worst I stand in need of a suit of cloths shoes <add hand="h1"
                        place="inline">No <del hand="h1">8</del>7</add> Hat pants <add hand="h1"
                        place="inline">35</add> &amp; coat <add hand="h1" place="inline"
                    >35</add> and also some under clothing if you send them you shall <add hand="h1"
                        place="inline">be</add> Duly Repaid for them as soon as time will admit
                    Direct in this way Franklin Carroll Prisoner of war <orig reg="Camp Chase">camp
                        chase</orig>
                    <orig reg="Ohio">ohio</orig>
                    <add hand="h1" place="inline">Prison B</add> in care of <abbr expan="Colonel"
                        >Col</abbr> Richardson commanding you wanted <orig reg="know">now</orig>
                    when I seen your Brother Real I seen him on <orig reg="Tye River">tye
                    river</orig> Nelson <abbr expan="County">
                        <orig reg="Co">co</orig>
                    </abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr> out <orig reg="refuging">Refugeing</orig>
                    Willie was along also <abbr expan="Esquire">Esq</abbr> Jacob Baylor Dr William
                    is Surgeon of the <del hand="h1">2</del>7 <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Infantry">Inftry</abbr> I saw your father on the 8 day of <orig
                        reg="May">may</orig> at D C <orig reg="Arehart's">Arehart</orig> Your
                    relations around home are still living John Brown is dead that married a <orig
                        reg="Miss Steel">miss steel</orig>
                    <abbr expan="Colonel">Col</abbr> W S H Baylor was killed at the 2 Battle of
                        <orig reg="Manassas">manassas</orig> W H Randolph is killed also I will
                    write to you again and give you the particular<unclear>s</unclear> John R Berry
                    Jr N E Miller Peraid Crist Jeramiah <del hand="h1">F</del>
                    Fro<unclear>x</unclear> all are here from <orig reg="Augusta">augusta</orig> to
                    when you send them clothes Send as I Directed and they will come safe</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>yours Truly</salute>
                    <signed>Franklin Carroll</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
